// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Permanent magnet synchronous motor coupled with gear transmission for precise motion control in MABI MAX 100 six-axis serial robot. Operates under Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl control system with input current I_M."
]

instance GearTransmission : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Cycloidal gear transmission system providing mechanical advantage and motion conversion for the robot's six axes. Integrated with permanent magnet synchronous motor for precise positioning."
]

instance SiemensSINUMERIK840DslController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Integrated control system for MABI MAX 100 robot executing command sequences and operational coordination. Supports individual axis control with position, speed, and acceleration inputs while managing safety constraints through closed-loop feedback."
]

// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance MotorEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Motor encoder mounted directly on permanent magnet synchronous motor shaft providing high-resolution time-series data of input current (I_M) and motor angle with encoder-based feedback for precise positioning."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorEncoderDataTransmitted
]

instance SecondaryEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Secondary encoder positioned behind gearbox measuring output angle with high spatial resolution. Provides time-series data for all monitored variables including output angle and motor current (I_M) for motion synchronization."
    DTDFVocab:producedData SecondaryEncoderDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance MotorEncoderDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Time-series data transmission from motor encoder including input current (I_M) and motor shaft angle. Transmitted via industry-standard industrial IoT protocols (OPC UA, MQTT, or HTTP/REST) with event-triggered sampling for real-time requirements."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorEncoder
]

instance SecondaryEncoderDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Time-series data transmission from secondary encoder including output angle and processed motor current (I_M) after gearbox. Transmitted via industry-standard industrial IoT protocols with optimized sampling for low-latency feedback."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom SecondaryEncoder
]

instance FrictionalForceDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Contextual data traces of frictional forces within first axis derived from motor and secondary encoder data. Aggregated for dynamic modeling and real-time behavior prediction in high-precision manufacturing."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorEncoder, SecondaryEncoder
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance GeometricModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Geometric representation of MABI MAX 100 six-axis serial robot including CAD-based structural components and kinematic chains. Implicitly referenced via SysML or specialized CAD tools for spatial relationships."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SysMLModelingFramework, MontiArcADL
]

instance BehavioralModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral dynamics of robot actuators and control system modeled using MontiArc Automaton or SysML state machines. Integrated with MathWorks Simulink for detailed behavior description and simulation."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo MontiArcADL, SimulinkSimulationTool
]

instance FrictionalForceAnalyticalModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Physics-based analytical model of frictional forces within first axis derived from motor and secondary encoder data. Used for accurate simulation and real-time behavior prediction in high-precision machining operations."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkSimulationTool, CppPhysicsEngine
]

instance MotorCurrentData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Structured time-series data of input current (I_M) from permanent magnet synchronous motor. Processed for noise reduction and normalization to ensure data quality for simulation and analysis."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorEncoderDataTransmitted, SecondaryEncoderDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkSimulationTool, MontiArcADL
]

instance OutputAngleData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Structured time-series data of output angle from secondary encoder after gear transmission. Aggregated with motor current data for precise motion synchronization and behavioral modeling."
    DTDFVocab:fromData SecondaryEncoderDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkSimulationTool, MontiArcADL
]

instance FrictionalForceData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated contextual data traces of frictional forces within first axis derived from motor current and output angle data. Used for dynamic modeling and real-time behavior prediction."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorEncoderDataTransmitted, SecondaryEncoderDataTransmitted, FrictionalForceDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkSimulationTool, CppPhysicsEngine
]

// C11: Enablers
instance SysMLModelingFramework : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Systems Modeling Language (SysML) framework for structuring system descriptions across multiple abstraction layers (requirements, functional architecture, logical architecture, and product/technical layers). Supports Internal Block Diagrams (IBDs) for architecture and state machines for behavior."
    DTDFVocab:enables DigitalShadowMonitoringService, BehavioralSimulationService
]

instance MontiArcADL : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Architecture Description Language (ADL) for modeling components, interfaces, and composition using MontiArc. Supports MontiArc Automaton for state-based behavior and integration with simulation tools."
    DTDFVocab:enables DigitalShadowMonitoringService, BehavioralSimulationService
]

instance SimulinkSimulationTool : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MathWorks Simulink tool for dynamic system simulation and co-simulation with other tools. Enables detailed behavioral modeling and real-time control algorithm implementation."
    DTDFVocab:enables BehavioralSimulationService, FrictionalForcePredictionService
]

instance CppPhysicsEngine : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Custom C++ implementation for physics-based analytical modeling of frictional forces. Provides high-performance computation for real-time behavior prediction."
    DTDFVocab:enables FrictionalForcePredictionService
]

instance DigitalShadowReferenceModel : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "UML class diagram-based framework for contextual data aggregation and abstraction in manufacturing. Defines one-way automated data flow from physical objects to digital representations."
    DTDFVocab:enables DigitalShadowMonitoringService
]

// C6: Services
instance DigitalShadowMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Passive collection of live measurement data from physical system (operational states, sensor readings) without bidirectional interaction. Aggregates contextual data traces for simulation and analysis."
    DTDFVocab:provides DigitalShadowInsight
]

instance BehavioralSimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Aggregation and abstraction of contextual data traces to simulate expected robot behavior. Enables offline analysis and behavioral forecasting using SysML and MontiArc models."
    DTDFVocab:provides BehavioralInsight
]

instance FrictionalForcePredictionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Dynamic modeling of frictional forces within first axis using analytical and simulation models. Enables real-time behavior prediction for high-precision machining operations."
    DTDFVocab:provides FrictionalForceInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance DigitalShadowInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Contextual data traces of robot operational states and sensor readings aggregated for passive monitoring and analysis. Used to identify performance trends and operational anomalies."
]

instance BehavioralInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Simulated behavioral predictions of robot motion and control system performance based on aggregated sensor data. Enables validation of control algorithms and operational scenarios."
]

instance FrictionalForceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time predictions of frictional forces within first axis enabling accurate compensation in machining operations. Used to optimize precision and reduce wear in high-precision applications."
]

// C1: Environment
instance MABIMax100RobotEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:contains PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor, GearTransmission, SiemensSINUMERIK840DslController,
                 MotorEncoder, SecondaryEncoder
]

// C5: Components
instance RobotActuationSystem : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Component integrating permanent magnet synchronous motor, gear transmission, and Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl controller for precise motion control in MABI MAX 100 robot."
]

instance RobotSensingSystem : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Component comprising motor encoder and secondary encoder providing high-resolution time-series data for all monitored variables including input current (I_M) and output angle."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin (DT) system’s orchestration and coordination are implicitly tied to **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) methodologies**, which integrate heterogeneous models (e.g., SysML for architecture, MontiArc Automaton for behavior, or Simulink for simulation). The document highlights the need for **architecture description languages (ADLs)** like ACME, AADL, or SysML Internal Block Diagrams (IBDs) to define **component & connector perspectives**, including interfaces, interconnections, and composition. For behavior, these are often combined with **simulation tools (e.g., MathWorks Simulink, other simulation methods [29]–[30])** or general-purpose languages (e.g., C++, Java). The **coordination mechanisms** are not explicitly detailed, but the integration of multiple modeling notations and tools suggests a **hybrid, service-oriented architecture** where components (e.g., digital shadows, active processing units) interact via standardized interfaces. Resource management is implied through the **abstraction and aggregation of contextual data traces** (as per the digital shadow reference model), but no specific orchestration patterns (e.g., microservices, event-driven) are mentioned."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system emphasizes **model fidelity** through **multi-layered abstraction** (requirements → functional → logical → physical), ensuring alignment between digital and physical system representations. **Validation and verification (V&V)** methods are implied but not detailed; however, the integration of **simulation tools** (e.g., Simulink) and **ADLs** (e.g., MontiArc Automaton) suggests formal verification techniques (e.g., state machine analysis) and **co-simulation** for behavioral accuracy. **Uncertainty sources** may arise from **data abstraction** (e.g., Digital Shadow aggregation) and **model simplification**, though quantification methods are not specified. **Error detection** could leverage **anomaly detection** in data streams or **model discrepancy analysis** (e.g., comparing simulated vs. real-world behavior). **Quality assurance** processes are inferred to include **traceability** across MBSE layers (e.g., SysML requirements links) and **toolchain consistency checks** (e.g., validating ADL-to-simulation mappings)."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The document does not provide explicit details on **data exchange protocols, interoperability standards, or dependencies on external systems** for Digital Twin (DT) integration. However, the **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) framework** (e.g., SysML, ADLs like AADL/ACME) inherently supports **heterogeneous system integration** by defining standardized interfaces and connectors between components. The use of **simulation tools (e.g., Simulink) or general-purpose languages (C++, Java)** suggests potential integration with enterprise systems via APIs or middleware, though no specific protocols (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT, REST) are referenced. The **digital shadow reference model** implies passive data collection, which may rely on external systems for active processing or real-time synchronization, but no integration patterns with other DTs or enterprise systems are described. The document emphasizes the need to **cope with models in different notations and tools**, hinting at a **mediation layer** (e.g., ontology-based or model transformation frameworks) for seamless horizontal integration."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system incorporates **physical safety measures** through the **MABI robotic arm's safety cell**, which restricts the maximum working range to **[-90°, 90°]** to prevent collisions or unsafe operations. **Communication security** is implemented via **MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry Transport)** as the protocol for streaming data between components, as referenced in [52] and [53]. However, the provided documents do **not** specify cybersecurity protocols (e.g., OAuth, TLS, or encryption standards), **access control mechanisms**, or **authentication systems**. The **Asset Administration Shell (AAS)** framework ([46], [47], [50]) is mentioned as a structural component for Digital Twin modeling but lacks explicit details on **role-based permissions**, **threat mitigation strategies**, or **risk assessment approaches**. No fail-safe mechanisms or safety-critical system validations are described in the context documents."
]